one of the things that comes up in lint is about setting up automatic backups <https://trello.com/c/0LGS7Kgc/217-disable-automatic-backups>
We’ve talked about it’s potential implications before, but have done nothing to intentionally set it up or to disable it.
I have concerns that allowing automatic backups will give the user the ability to load the app on unsupported devices
but I do not know how it actually works
I wanted to just disable it, but I suppose I should see what happens first..
we should probably disable it
there's not a good argument to support it, i suppose
since the OS wont automatically re-set the live wallpaper in the event of a restore
I was thinking the images for moments would be cool to keep, but even those are probably not backed up, we’d have a lot of broken links
I’m disabling it now
